DZWERANI outside Vuwani in Limpopo is a hunting ground for thugs. On Sunday, residents spotted a bakkie which was allegedly used as a getaway car at many crime scenes. Angry residents attacked the driver, from nearby Lwamondo Village, and burnt his vehicle. The alleged thief was taken away to point out his accomplices. One angry resident said they are gatvol of the crime in their area. “We are sick and tired of these hooligans. We report them to the police but nothing is done. “We decided to take the law into our own hands and wipe out crime here.” Another resident said they had started security units and go out on patrol every evening.